1. Definitions

"Software" means the OnePlus 6T Arch Linux Installer project materials owned
by Toni McQueen and distributed with this licence, including installer
scripts, build scripts, profile glue, project-authored configuration files,
project documentation, project-owned boot or marketing assets, and updates
supplied under this licence.

"Software" does not include third-party code, third-party configuration files,
firmware, kernel source, kernel patches owned by other authors, postmarketOS
boot artifacts, Arch Linux ARM packages, vendor source trees, libraries,
protocol specifications, trademarks, or any material listed in
docs/THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md. Those materials remain under their own licences.

"Project Notice Files" means LICENSE, NOTICE, docs/THIRD-PARTY-NOTICES.md,
and any file-level copyright, attribution, provenance, or licence notice
distributed with the Software.

"Modified Version" means any version of the Software that is patched,
translated, adapted, decompiled and recompiled, combined with Software-derived
code, or otherwise modified in a way that requires permission from the
copyright holder. Independently created programs that merely communicate with
the Software through a documented, general-purpose interface are not Modified
Versions solely because of that communication.

"Corresponding Modification Materials" means the complete preferred materials
needed to understand, reproduce, build, install, and run a Modified Version,
including source code, binary patches, build scripts, configuration changes,
toolchain instructions, and modification documentation. Materials unrelated to
the modification do not need to be provided.

"Commercial Purpose" means use intended to obtain direct or indirect
commercial advantage or monetary compensation. It includes:

- sale, licensing, paid distribution, or paid access;
- use in a product, subscription, hosted service, or paid client deliverable;
- internal business use that materially supports revenue-generating activity;
- bundling with commercial hardware, software, training, or support;
- use supported by advertising, sponsorship, or product-linked donations;
- use by a contractor or Affiliate for any of the above; and
- avoiding these conditions by providing access to functionality over a
  network instead of distributing a copy.

"Affiliate" means an entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under
common control with another entity.

"Non-Commercial Purpose" means personal use, education, academic research,
charitable activity, hobby development, evaluation, or non-commercial
redistribution without commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

