3. Notices and Attribution

Every copy or substantial portion of the Software must include this licence,
the copyright notice above, the supplied NOTICE file, and the supplied
third-party notices. A Modified Version must be clearly marked as modified and
identify the modifier, date, and material changes.

Project Notice Files must be retained in source distributions, binary
distributions, installer archives, phone images, boot/root image bundles,
documentation bundles, mirrors, forks, and hosted download pages. If the
distribution format cannot preserve the original file layout, the same notices
must be reproduced in an obvious documentation or about/legal location.

Copyright, attribution, funding, contact, and provenance notices included in
the Software must not be removed, hidden, or misrepresented in redistributed
copies. A technical compatibility change may alter runtime display of a notice
only when the Project Notice Files remain intact and the redistribution still
provides clear attribution to Toni McQueen.

4. Mandatory Share-Back

Anyone who creates a Modified Version must provide the copyright holder,
without charge, with:

- the complete modified executable, image, installer, or binary artifact; and
- all Corresponding Modification Materials.

Delivery must occur no later than 30 days after the Modified Version is first
run, tested, published, made available to another person, or used for any
purpose, whichever occurs first. Delivery may be made through
https://github.com/ToniMcQueen/oneplus6t-install-linux-Arch-on-arm-845 or another method
designated by the copyright holder.

The required materials must be sufficient for the copyright holder to inspect,
reproduce, build, install, and run the Modified Version. When applicable, this
includes a complete source tree or patch series, build scripts, package
manifests, configuration files, generated image metadata, checksums, commit
identifiers, toolchain notes, and instructions for applying the changes.

The share-back obligation applies even when the Modified Version is used only
internally or made available through a network. It does not require disclosure
of independent programs or confidential information that is unrelated to the
modification.

Failure to provide the share-back materials on time is a licence breach even
if the Modified Version was never sold, published, advertised, or distributed
outside the modifier's own organisation.

5. Redistribution of Modified Versions

A redistributed Modified Version must remain under O6T-LINUX-1.0. No
additional term may remove or weaken the non-commercial, attribution, notice,
or share-back conditions. This clause does not alter the licence of an
independent work merely aggregated with the Software.

Redistributors must not describe a Modified Version as the official Toni
McQueen release unless it is the unmodified official release. Modified
Versions must use a different name or a clear modifier label, and must not
create confusion about source, sponsorship, endorsement, support, or update
responsibility.

No redistributed copy may use technical measures, private update gates, access
controls, obfuscation, or packaging tricks to avoid the notice, attribution,
non-commercial, or share-back conditions.

