9. Termination and Cure

Rights under this licence terminate automatically upon breach. For a first
breach, rights are reinstated if the breach is fully cured within 30 days after
the person discovers it or receives notice, whichever occurs first. Repeated,
wilful, or uncured breaches require express written reinstatement.

After termination, the person or entity in breach must stop using, copying,
modifying, distributing, hosting, advertising, or providing access to the
Software and any Modified Version unless and until rights are reinstated.
Termination does not remove obligations that by their nature must survive,
including notice retention, attribution, share-back, third-party licence
compliance, warranty disclaimer, liability limitation, and governing law.

